zpen (0.1.6-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Persistent preferences: the selected color, active tool, pen thickness,
    line style (solid/dashed) and text font size are now saved to
    ~/.zpen/config on exit and restored on the next launch.
  * Color palette: added a short horizontal indicator to the left of the
    first color showing the current pen thickness and dash pattern. The
    indicator refreshes whenever thickness (+ / - / 0) or dash style (*)
    changes.
  * Color palette: the white selection ring around the active color is now
    rendered at a fixed 1 px width and no longer scales with the pen
    thickness/dash style.

 -- Marco Aurélio Zoqui <marco@zoqui.com>  Wed, 13 May 2026 18:00:00 +0000

zpen (0.1.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Text tool: runtime font-size control. Ctrl++/Ctrl+- adjust the font size
    in 2 px steps (range 8–72 px); Ctrl+0 resets to the 18 px default. Works
    with numpad +/-/0 as well. Line spacing now tracks the active font size.

 -- Marco Aurélio Zoqui <marco@zoqui.com>  Wed, 13 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

zpen (0.1.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Bound `}` and `]` to the curly brace and square bracket tools, mirroring
    the existing `{` and `[` shortcuts.

 -- Marco Aurélio Zoqui <marco@zoqui.com>  Tue, 12 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

zpen (0.1.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Hardened temp-file handling: removed predictable /tmp paths in screenshot,
    paste, and OCR code paths; switched to mkstemp under XDG_RUNTIME_DIR.
  * Replaced shell-invoking system() calls with fork/execvp for xclip and
    tesseract integration.
  * Eliminated PPM intermediate; PNG is now written directly from the X image
    with overflow-safe size arithmetic.
  * NULL-checked XLoadQueryFont to fix a SEGV when the helvetica bitmap font
    is unavailable.

 -- Marco Aurélio Zoqui <marco@zoqui.com>  Fri, 08 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
